<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910731-0068</DOCNO><DOCID>910731-0068.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- MIPS Computer Systems Inc.:   Concern Has $597,000 Loss,   Declares Restructuring Plan</HL><DATE>07/31/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MIPS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   MIPS Computer Systems Inc. posted a second-quarter lossdespite increasing revenue, and announced a corporaterestructuring program to help it climb back towardprofitability.   In the period ended June 30, MIPS reported a loss of$597,000 or three cents a share, compared with year-earlierprofit of $4 million, or 16 cents a share. Revenue rose 13%to $44.5 million from $39.6 million. In nationalover-the-counter trading, MIPS shares closed at $15.25, up12.5 cents.</LP><TEXT>   The restructuring plan will include expense controls,salary reductions, and a &quot;voluntary incentive plan intendedto reduce the work force&quot; by an unspecified amount. MIPSexpects to incur &quot;significant costs&quot; related to therestructuring, the company added.   MIPS, based in Sunnyvale, Calif., is a supplier ofcomputer systems and other electronics products based on RISC(or reduced instruction-set computing) technology.</TEXT></DOC>